17-Mile Drive.label: 17-Mile Drive
17-Mile Drive.description: 17-Mile Drive is a scenic road through Pebble Beach and Pacific Grove on the Monterey Peninsula in California, much of which hugs the Pacific coastline and passes famous golf courses, mansions and scenic ... Wikipedia

A1 (Bosnia and Herzegovina).label: A1
A1 (Bosnia and Herzegovina).description: The A1 motorway is a motorway in Bosnia and Herzegovina that is part of the Corridor Vc and, together with two Croatian motorways and the Hungarian M6, will provide a modern and fast road connection ... Wikipedia

A1 (Croatia).label: A1
A1 (Croatia).description: The A1 motorway is the longest motorway in Croatia, spanning 465.5 kilometers. As it connects Zagreb, the nation's capital, to Split, the second largest city in the country and the largest city in ... Wikipedia

A1 autostrada (Poland).label: A1 autostrada
A1 autostrada (Poland).description: The autostrada A1 in Poland is a north-south motorway under construction that will run through central Poland, from Gdańsk on the Baltic Sea through Łódź and the Upper Silesian Industry Area to the ... Wikipedia

A1 motorway (Netherlands).label: A1 motorway
A1 motorway (Netherlands).description: The A1 is a motorway in the Netherlands. The road connects the city of Amsterdam, near the interchange Watergraafsmeer, with the German border, near Oldenzaal and Bad Bentheim, and the German Autobahn BAB 30. Wikipedia

A2 motorway (Switzerland).label: A2 motorway
A2 motorway (Switzerland).description: The A2 is a motorway in Switzerland. It forms Switzerland's main north-south axis from Basel to Chiasso, meandering with a slight drift toward the east. Wikipedia

A5 (Croatia).label: A5
A5 (Croatia).description: The A5 motorway is a motorway in Croatia spanning 55.5 kilometres. It connects Osijek, the largest city in Slavonia region, to the Croatian motorway network at the Sredanci interchange of the A3 motorway. Wikipedia

A6 motorway (Switzerland).label: A6 motorway
A6 motorway (Switzerland).description: The A6 motorway, an Autobahn in Switzerland, connects Biel / Bienne over Bern with Thun. The A6 is located entirely within the Canton of Berne and, in particular, has a great regional significance, so ... Wikipedia

A9 (Croatia).label: A9
A9 (Croatia).description: The A9 motorway is a north–south motorway in Croatia, with a length of 78.3 kilometres. Beginning in Pula, the largest city on the Istrian peninsula, it runs north to the Croatian motorway and expressway network at the Kanfanar interchange. Wikipedia

Autostrada A18 (Italy).label: Autostrada A18
Autostrada A18 (Italy).description: The Autostrada A18 is a 77 km motorway on the Ionian coast of Sicily that links Messina to Catania. The motorway is linked to the A20 Messina-Palermo at its northern-end and to the A19 Palermo-Catania ... Wikipedia

Autostrada A19 (Italy).label: Autostrada A19
Autostrada A19 (Italy).description: The Autostrada A19 is a 199 km motorway on the island of Sicily that links Palermo to Catania. The motorway from Palermo follows the Tyrrhenian coast esatwards for 46 km and then turns south to go over ... Wikipedia

Autostrada A26 (Italy).label: Autostrada A26
Autostrada A26 (Italy).description: The Autostrada A26 is a motorway in the northwestern Italian regions of Liguria and Piedmont. It is named the Autostrada dei Trafori after the numerous tunnels through which it passes, both Apennine and Subalpine. Wikipedia

Birdsville Track.label: Birdsville Track
Birdsville Track.description: The Birdsville Track is a notable outback road in Australia. The 517 km track runs from Marree, a small town in northern South Australia, north across the Tirari Desert and Sturt Stony Desert, ending in Birdsville in south western Queensland. Wikipedia

Carnaby Street.label: Carnaby Street
Carnaby Street.description: Carnaby Street is a pedestrianised shopping street in the City of Westminster, London, located in the Soho district, near Oxford Street and Regent Street. Wikipedia

Church Street, Monmouth.label: Church Street, Monmouth
Church Street, Monmouth.description: Church Street is a pedestrianised street in the centre of Monmouth, Wales. It now contains a variety of independent shops, restaurants, commercial art galleries, and the Savoy Theatre. Wikipedia

D1 motorway (Czech Republic).label: D1 motorway
D1 motorway (Czech Republic).description: D1 motorway is the main highway of the Czech Republic. Currently it connects the two biggest Czech cities, Prague and Brno, in the future it will link Ostrava and to the Czech-Polish border in Věřňovice / Gorzyczki. Wikipedia

D4 motorway (Slovakia).label: D4 motorway
D4 motorway (Slovakia).description: D4 is a motorway in southwestern Slovakia. The planned highway is commonly referred to as the Bratislava bypass. Currently there is only a short stretch from Austrian border at Jarovce to the junction with D2, opened in 1998. Wikipedia

D5 motorway (Czech Republic).label: D5 motorway
D5 motorway (Czech Republic).description: D5 motorway is a highway in the Czech Republic. It runs from Prague through Pilsen into Germany. D5 is 151 km long; a bypass of Pilsen includes the 380 metre long Valík Tunnel and the 445 metre long bridge over the River Úhlava. Wikipedia

Fosse Way.label: Fosse Way
Fosse Way.description: The Fosse Way was a Roman road in England that linked Exeter in South West England to Lincoln in Lincolnshire, via Ilchester, Bath, Cirencester and Leicester. Wikipedia

Great Ocean Road.label: Great Ocean Road
Great Ocean Road.description: The Great Ocean Road is an Australian National Heritage listed 243 kilometres stretch of road along the south-eastern coast of Australia between the Victorian cities of Torquay and Allansford. Wikipedia

Great River Road.label: Great River Road
Great River Road.description: The Great River Road is a collection of state and local roads which follow the course of the Mississippi River through ten states of the United States. Wikipedia

Highway 1 (Israel).label: Highway 1
Highway 1 (Israel).description: Highway 1, is the main highway connecting Tel Aviv and Jerusalem in Israel. Wikipedia

Highway 2 (Israel).label: Highway 2
Highway 2 (Israel).description: Highway 2 is an Israeli highway located on the coastal plain of the Mediterranean Sea. It begins a major arterial road within Tel Aviv, becoming a freeway as it exits the city northward continuing to Haifa. Wikipedia

Highway 3 (Israel).label: Highway 3
Highway 3 (Israel).description: Highway 3 is a highway in Israel. It begins at Highway 4 on the outskirts of Ashkelon, running east-northeast, passing through Kiryat Malakhi and Latrun, and ending just short of Modi'in. Wikipedia

Highway 4 (Israel).label: Highway 4
Highway 4 (Israel).description: Highway 4 is an Israeli highway that runs along Israel's entire coastal plain of the Mediterranean Sea, its route in the north runs from the Rosh HaNikra border crossing with Lebanon until the Erez Border Crossing with the Gaza Strip. Wikipedia

Highway 5 (Israel).label: Highway 5
Highway 5 (Israel).description: Highway 5, or the Trans-Samaria Highway, is one of Israel's main highways, connecting the Mediterranean coast immediately north of Tel Aviv with the central Sharon plain and eastwards to Ariel and other ... Wikipedia

Highway 6 (Israel).label: Highway 6
Highway 6 (Israel).description: Highway 6, also known as the Trans-Israel Highway, is a major electronic toll highway in Israel.Highway 6 is the first Israeli Build-Operate-Transfer road constructed, carried out mainly by the private ... Wikipedia

Icefields Parkway.label: Icefields Parkway
Icefields Parkway.description: The Icefields Parkway, also known as Highway 93 north, is a scenic road in Alberta, Canada. It parallels the Continental Divide, traversing the rugged landscape of the Canadian Rockies, travelling ... Wikipedia

Interstate 238.label: Interstate 238
Interstate 238.description: Interstate 238 is a short auxiliary route of the Interstate Highway System in the San Francisco Bay Area in the U.S. state of California. Wikipedia

Interstate 5 in Washington.label: Interstate 5 in Washington
Interstate 5 in Washington.description: Interstate 5 in Washington is a 276.62-mile highway in the U.S. state of Washington that extends from its border with Oregon to its border with Canada. Wikipedia

Interstate H-1.label: Interstate H-1
Interstate H-1.description: Interstate H-1 is the busiest Interstate Highway in Hawaii, United States, located on the island of O‘ahu. Despite the number, this is an east–west highway—the 'H'-series numbering reflects the order in which routes were funded and built. Wikipedia

Interstate H-2.label: Interstate H-2
Interstate H-2.description: Interstate H-2 is an intrastate Interstate Highway located on the island of O‘ahu in Hawai‘i, USA. H-2 is also known as the Veterans Memorial Freeway. Wikipedia

Interstate H-3.label: Interstate H-3
Interstate H-3.description: Interstate H-3 is an intrastate Interstate Highway located on the island of O'ahu in the state of Hawai'i in the United States. H-3 is also known as the John A. Burns Freeway. Wikipedia

Mühlviertler Schnellstraße.label: Mühlviertler Schnellstraße
Mühlviertler Schnellstraße.description: Mühlviertler Schnellstraße is an under construction schnellstraße in Austria. One 1,970-metre section of the Neumarkt tunnel is already in operation. Wikipedia

M11 motorway.label: M11 motorway
M11 motorway.description: The M11 is a motorway in England running approximately north from the North Circular Road in South Woodford in northeast London to the A14, northwest of Cambridge. Wikipedia

M15 motorway (Hungary).label: M15 motorway
M15 motorway (Hungary).description: The M15 motorway is a Hungarian motorway connects the M1 motorway to Bratislava, the capital of Slovakia. The Hungary-Slovakia border crossing is at Rajka (Hungary) and Čunovo. Wikipedia

M1 motorway (Northern Ireland).label: M1 motorway
M1 motorway (Northern Ireland).description: The M1 is a motorway in Northern Ireland. It is the longest motorway in Northern Ireland and runs for 38 miles from Belfast to Dungannon through County Down and County Armagh. Wikipedia

M7 motorway (Hungary).label: M7 motorway
M7 motorway (Hungary).description: The M7 motorway is a Hungarian motorway which runs from Budapest towards the Croatian border at Letenye, reaching Székesfehérvár, then Siófok, a town on Lake Balaton, and the city of Nagykanizsa in the southwest of the country. Wikipedia

Mainzer Landstraße.label: Mainzer Landstraße
Mainzer Landstraße.description: Mainzer Landstraße is one of the main arterial roads in Frankfurt am Main, running west from the city centre to the outlying suburbs of the city. Wikipedia

Ost Autobahn.label: Ost Autobahn
Ost Autobahn.description: The Ost Autobahn A4 or "Eastern Motorway" is part of the European route E60 and goes from Vienna to the town of Nickelsdorf, on the Hungarian border. Wikipedia

R4 expressway (Czech Republic).label: R4 expressway
R4 expressway (Czech Republic).description:
Expressway R4 is an expressway in Czech Republic, southwest from Prague.
Sections of the expressway Wikipedia

R52 expressway (Czech Republic).label: R52 expressway
R52 expressway (Czech Republic).description: Expressway R52 is an expressway in the South Moravian Region of the Czech Republic, currently leading from Modřice, about 7 km south of Brno, to Pohořelice, parallel to the Highway D2. It forms part of the European Route E461. Wikipedia

Reeperbahn.label: Reeperbahn
Reeperbahn.description: The Reeperbahn is a street in Hamburg's St. Pauli district, one of the two centres of Hamburg's nightlife and also the city's red-light district. In German it is also sometimes described as die sündigste Meile. Wikipedia

Route 3 (Uruguay).label: Route 3
Route 3 (Uruguay).description: Route 3 is a national route of Uruguay. In 1975, it was assigned the name General José Artigas, a national hero of Uruguay. Wikipedia

Südost Autobahn.label: Südost Autobahn
Südost Autobahn.description: The Südost Autobahn is a motorway, or ‘Autobahn’, in Austria. It runs from the Süd Autobahn at the junction Knoten Guntramsdorf southeast to Eisenstadt. Wikipedia

Sognefjellsvegen.label: Sognefjellsvegen
Sognefjellsvegen.description: The Sognefjellsvegen or Sognefjellsveien is the highest mountain pass road in Northern Europe. Part of County Road 55, it is located in Oppland and Sogn og Fjordane counties in Norway. Wikipedia

Stanegate.label: Stanegate
Stanegate.description: The Stanegate, or "stone road", was an important Roman road built in what is now northern England. It linked two forts that guarded important river crossings; Corstopitum in the east, situated on Dere Street, and Luguvalium in the west. Wikipedia

Top of the World Highway.label: Top of the World Highway
Top of the World Highway.description: The Top of the World Highway is a 127-kilometre long highway, beginning at a junction with the Taylor Highway near Jack Wade, Alaska traveling east to its terminus at the ferry terminal in West Dawson, on the western banks of the Yukon River. Wikipedia

Washington State Route 10.label: Washington State Route 10
Washington State Route 10.description: State Route 10 is a 16.16-mile-long state highway in the U.S. state of Washington. The highway is a remnant of U.S. Route 10 in Kittitas County, traveling southeast along the Yakima River from SR 970 in Teanaway to US 97 northwest of Ellensburg. Wikipedia

Washington State Route 11.label: Washington State Route 11
Washington State Route 11.description: State Route 11 is a 21.28-mile long state highway that serves Skagit and Whatcom counties in the U.S. state of Washington. Wikipedia

Watling Street.label: Watling Street
Watling Street.description: Watling Street is the name given to an ancient trackway in England and Wales that was first used by the Britons mainly between the modern cities of Canterbury and St Albans. Wikipedia

A3 motorway (Tunisia).label: A3 motorway
A3 motorway (Tunisia).description: TheA3' links Tunis capital of Tunisia, the village of Oued Zarga. Eventually, the highway linking the capital to the border Algeria nne through Bou Salem, or 217 miles across the Tunisian territory. Wikipedia

Autovia B-24.label: Autovia B-24
Autovia B-24.description:
The Autovia B-24 is a highway in Spain. The road connects Barcelona to the towns of Penedès.
It starts at a junction with the Autovía A-2 south of the City centre. The road is under construction and will form an upgrade of the start of the N-340. Wikipedia

Autovia C-12.label: Autovia C-12
Autovia C-12.description: The C-12 is a highway in Catalonia, Spain, that connects Lleida with Tortosa and the Ebre river delta. For much of its length it runs along the lower Ebre valley. North of Lleida the road follows the Noguera valley before joining the C-13. Wikipedia

Autovia C-13.label: Autovia C-13
Autovia C-13.description: The C-13, also known as Eix del Pallars, is a highway in Catalonia, Spain, that connects Lleida with Balaguer and the eastern Noguera Pallaresa river valley. North of Tremp. The road joins the N-260 Wikipedia

Autovia C-14.label: Autovia C-14
Autovia C-14.description:
The C-14 is a highway in Catalonia, Spain from La Seu d'Urgell to Salou through Reus.
Nowadays is a highway from Salou to Reus and in the future the rest of the C-14 road will be upgraded to a highway. Wikipedia

Autovia C-60.label: Autovia C-60
Autovia C-60.description: The Autovia C-60, also known as the Autovia Mataró-Granollers is a highway in Catalonia, Spain. This is a freeway that connects Mataró and Granollers. Wikipedia

European route E4.label: European route E4
European route E4.description: European route E 4 passes from north to south through Sweden from the border with Finland, with a total length of 1,590 kilometres. The Finnish part lies entirely within Tornio in northern Finland, and is actually only 800 metres long. Wikipedia

Oxford Street.label: Oxford Street
Oxford Street.description: Oxford Street is a major road in the City of Westminster in the West End of London. It is Europe's busiest shopping street, and as of 2011 had approximately 300 shops. Wikipedia

East 161st Street (Bronx).label: East 161st Street
East 161st Street (Bronx).description: East 161st Street is a short, major thoroughfare in the southern portion of the Bronx. The road is 1.6 mile long and is the best access to the Yankee Stadium. Wikipedia

East 233rd Street (Bronx).label: East 233rd Street
East 233rd Street (Bronx).description: East 233rd Street is one of the major thoroughfares in the Bronx. The road is 3 miles long and stretches from U.S. Route 1 in the Eastchester section of the Bronx to the Major Deegan Expressway in Woodlawn. Wikipedia

New York State Route 9X.label: New York State Route 9X
New York State Route 9X.description: New York State Route 9X was a state highway located within New York City. It served as an alternate route of U.S. Route 9 through Manhattan and the Bronx. Wikipedia

Pelham Parkway.label: Pelham Parkway
Pelham Parkway.description: Pelham Parkway or Bronx Park East is primarily a residential neighborhood geographically located in the center of the Bronx borough of New York City in the United States. The neighborhood is part of Bronx Community Board 11. Wikipedia

Saint Catherine Street.label: Saint Catherine Street
Saint Catherine Street.description: Saint Catherine Street is the primary commercial artery of Downtown Montreal, Quebec, Canada. It crosses the central business district from west to east, beginning at the corner of Claremont Avenue and ... Wikipedia

Main Street, Gibraltar.label: Main Street, Gibraltar
Main Street, Gibraltar.description: Main Street is the main arterial street in the British overseas territory of Gibraltar. Wikipedia

Connaught Square.label: Connaught Square
Connaught Square.description: Connaught Square, in the City of Westminster, was the first square of city houses to be built in the Bayswater area. It was named after the Duke of Gloucester, who had a house nearby. The current appearance of the square dates from the 1820s. Wikipedia

Tri-State Tollway.label: Tri-State Tollway
Tri-State Tollway.description: The Tri-State Tollway is a U.S. toll road maintained by the Illinois State Toll Highway Authority in northeastern Illinois which is considered one of the most heavily traveled highways in the country. Wikipedia

Farm to Market Road 1626.label: Farm to Market Road 1626
Farm to Market Road 1626.description: Farm to Market Road 1626, or FM 1626 is a farm to market road, a state maintained road which serves to connect rural and agricultural areas to market towns, in the U.S. state of Texas. It is located in Travis and Hays counties. Wikipedia

National Highway 218 (India).label: National Highway 218
National Highway 218 (India).description: National Highway 218 is a national highway of India. This highway connects four main cities in northern part of Karnataka state namely, Gulbarga, Bagalkote, Bijapur and Hubli. It covers a distance of 399 km. Wikipedia

111 Street, Edmonton.label: 111 Street, Edmonton
111 Street, Edmonton.description: 111 Street is a major arterial road in south Edmonton, Alberta, Canada. The south leg of the LRT runs for most of its length, between the northbound and southbound lanes. Wikipedia

66 Street, Edmonton.label: 66 Street, Edmonton
66 Street, Edmonton.description: 66 Street is the designated name of two major arterial roads and a short rural road in east Edmonton, Alberta, Canada, separated by the North Saskatchewan River. Wikipedia

Academician Sakharov Avenue, Moscow.label: Academician Sakharov Avenue, Moscow
Academician Sakharov Avenue, Moscow.description: Academician Sakharov Prospect is a street in the center of Moscow, in Krasnoselsky District. In the south, the street is limited by Turgenevskaya Square and the Boulevard Ring. Wikipedia

Azadegan Expressway.label: Azadegan Expressway
Azadegan Expressway.description: Azadegan Expressway or Tehran Ringway is an expressway in southern Tehran. It connects Tehran-Mashhad Highway to Tehran-Karaj-Tabriz Freeway and Tehran-Shomal Freeway Wikipedia

Bangsar – Petaling Jaya Bypass.label: Bangsar – Petaling Jaya Bypass
Bangsar – Petaling Jaya Bypass.description: The Bangsar-Petaling Jaya Bypass or Lebuhraya Pintasan Bangsar-Petaling Jaya is a major highway in Kuala Lumpur city, Malaysia. The highway passing Mid Valley City from Bangsar to Federal Highway. Wikipedia
